Chester Makana, News24 Correspondent(File) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Polokwane - A prominent lawyer allegedly&nbsp;implicated in a farm shooting is set to appear&nbsp;in the Thabamoopo Magistrate's Court on Friday. He was arrested after four people were shot and wounded&nbsp;on the&nbsp;Zebediela Citrus farm on Thursday.It was alleged the suspect had a meeting with some of the employees in his company offices there and during the meeting, a fight ensued.The suspect allegedly pulled out a firearm and shot four&nbsp;people aged 32 ,50, 52 and 38 years, before fleeing the scene&nbsp;in his vehicle. "The injured employees were taken to the hospital with gun shot wounds for medical treatment after receiving the first aid from the local clinic," said police spokesperson&nbsp;Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.